{"title":"Pro Log: Tadej Pogačar and Grace Brown win Liège-Bastogne-Liège, women’s Milan-San Remo news and Lorena Wiebes extends SD Worx-Protime contract","link":"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/pro-cycling-news-liege-bastogne-liege-2024","date":1713807145000,"content":"<p><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a><br />\n<a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/pro-cycling-news-liege-bastogne-liege-2024\">Pro Log: Tadej Pogačar and Grace Brown win Liège-Bastogne-Liège, women’s Milan-San Remo news and Lorena Wiebes extends SD Worx-Protime contract</a></p>\n\n<p>Welcome back to another edition of <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/tags/pro-log\" target=\"_blank\">Pro Log</a>. This past weekend marked the final <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/all-you-need-to-know-about-the-classics-monuments-cobbles\" target=\"_blank\">spring Classic</a> as we transition to <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/giro-ditalia-watch-live-stages-route-riders-teams-start-list\" target=\"_blank\">Grand Tour season</a>. How time flies.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The men’s <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/tags/liege-bastogne-liege\" target=\"_blank\">Liège-Bastogne-Liège</a> was won by <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/tags/tadej-pogacar\" target=\"_blank\">Tadej Pogačar</a> (UAE Team Emirates) through another solo attack while Grace Brown (FDJ-Suez) sprinted to victory in the women’s race.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The Tour of Turkey got underway yesterday and Max Kanter (Astana Qazaqstan) won Stage 2 from Kemer to Kalkan with Henri Uhlig (Alpecin-Deceuninck) leading the race.</p>\n\n\n<div>\r\n                <div>\r\n                   <div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <h4><span>Related Posts</span></h4>\r\n                      </div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <div>\r\n                            <div>\r\n                            <article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/kasia-niewiadoma-fleche-wallonne\">Kasia Niewiadoma is cycling’s latest example for why you should never give up</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/tadej-pogacar-monument-ranking\">Every Tadej Pogačar Monument performance ranked</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/giro-ditalia-watch-live-stages-route-riders-teams-start-list\">Giro d’Italia 2024: Stage-by-stage preview and how to watch</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article></div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <span></span><span></span><span></span>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                \r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        </div>\n\n\n<h2>Tadej Pogačar solos to second Liège-Bastogne-Liège victory</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/Tadej-Pogacar-at-Liege-Bastogne-Liege-2024-970x647.jpeg\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/Tadej-Pogacar-at-Liege-Bastogne-Liege-2024-970x646.jpeg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/Tadej-Pogacar-at-Liege-Bastogne-Liege-2024-300x200.jpeg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/Tadej-Pogacar-at-Liege-Bastogne-Liege-2024-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/Tadej-Pogacar-at-Liege-Bastogne-Liege-2024-1536x1025.jpeg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/Tadej-Pogacar-at-Liege-Bastogne-Liege-2024-750x500.jpeg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/Tadej-Pogacar-at-Liege-Bastogne-Liege-2024-1140x760.jpeg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/Tadej-Pogacar-at-Liege-Bastogne-Liege-2024-465x310.jpeg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/Tadej-Pogacar-at-Liege-Bastogne-Liege-2024-620x413.jpeg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/Tadej-Pogacar-at-Liege-Bastogne-Liege-2024-350x233.jpeg 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/Tadej-Pogacar-at-Liege-Bastogne-Liege-2024.jpeg 2048w\" /><figcaption>A.S.O./Billy Ceusters</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>It was not a question of if Tadej Pogačar (UAE Team Emirates) would attack at Liège-Bastogne-Liège, but when. Fresh from an altitude training camp, he lined up at the start line alongside <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/tags/mathieu-van-der-poel\" target=\"_blank\">Mathieu van der Poel</a> (Alpecin-Deceuninck), who in turn was arriving off the back of his <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/tags/tour-of-flanders\" target=\"_blank\">Tour of Flanders</a> and <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/tags/paris-roubaix\" target=\"_blank\">Paris-Roubaix</a> dominance. Unstoppable force versus immovable object. Who would prevail?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Pogačar attacked on the iconic Côte de la Redoute climb with just under 39km to the finish. This is also where last year’s victor <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/tags/remco-evenepoel\" target=\"_blank\">Remco Evenepoel</a> (Soudal-QuickStep) went clear. But this was a far cry from Pogačar’s 2023 Liège-Bastogne-Liège, which ended in a broken wrist and shattered Ardennes triple dreams. He rode clear and dedicated the win to his partner Urška Žigart’s mother, who sadly passed away on that day two years ago.</p>\n\n\n\n<div><blockquote><p>Une 2⃣eme place qui signifie beaucoup pour <a href=\"https://twitter.com/romainbardet?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\" target=\"_blank\">@romainbardet</a> sur <a href=\"https://twitter.com/hashtag/LBL?src=hash&amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\" target=\"_blank\">#LBL</a> <img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/14.0.0/72x72/1f972.png\" alt=\"🥲\" /><br /><br />A special 2⃣nd place for <a href=\"https://twitter.com/romainbardet?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\" target=\"_blank\">@romainbardet</a> in <a href=\"https://twitter.com/hashtag/LBL?src=hash&amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\" target=\"_blank\">#LBL</a> <img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/14.0.0/72x72/1f972.png\" alt=\"🥲\" /> <a href=\"https://t.co/wHkG4fFsP8\" target=\"_blank\">https://t.co/wHkG4fFsP8</a> <a href=\"https://t.co/6XaCEvEb53\" target=\"_blank\">pic.twitter.com/6XaCEvEb53</a></p>— Liège-Bastogne-Liège (@LiegeBastogneL) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/LiegeBastogneL/status/1782059922210894066?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\" target=\"_blank\">April 21, 2024</a></blockquote> </div>\n\n\n\n<p>Behind Pogačar, Romain Bardet (DSM-Firmenich-PostNL) finished second, a career best Monument performance. On his way to the podium, Bardet gave a thumbs up to the camera, smiling at his success and after the finish the emotions came flooding in, as he was seen sobbing on his bike at the achievement. Van der Poel won the sprint for third place. Even Bardet’s son couldn’t believe it.</p>\n\n\n\n<div><blockquote><p>This is so cute <br />Angus almost crying saying he didn't know his dad could beat Mathieu <a href=\"https://t.co/UrwDberjqC\" target=\"_blank\">pic.twitter.com/UrwDberjqC</a></p>— allergy_al<img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/14.0.0/72x72/1f438.png\" alt=\"🐸\" /><img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/14.0.0/72x72/1f3b8.png\" alt=\"🎸\" /><img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/14.0.0/72x72/1f3a4.png\" alt=\"🎤\" /> (@allergy_al) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/allergy_al/status/1782321290528841892?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\" target=\"_blank\">April 22, 2024</a></blockquote> </div>\n\n\n\n<h2>Grace Brown sprints to win at Liège-Bastogne-Liège Femmes</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"646\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/Grace-Brown-wins-Liege-Bastogne-Liege-2024-970x646.jpeg\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/Grace-Brown-wins-Liege-Bastogne-Liege-2024-970x646.jpeg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/Grace-Brown-wins-Liege-Bastogne-Liege-2024-300x200.jpeg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/Grace-Brown-wins-Liege-Bastogne-Liege-2024-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/Grace-Brown-wins-Liege-Bastogne-Liege-2024-1536x1023.jpeg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/Grace-Brown-wins-Liege-Bastogne-Liege-2024-750x500.jpeg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/Grace-Brown-wins-Liege-Bastogne-Liege-2024-1140x759.jpeg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/Grace-Brown-wins-Liege-Bastogne-Liege-2024-465x310.jpeg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/Grace-Brown-wins-Liege-Bastogne-Liege-2024-620x413.jpeg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/Grace-Brown-wins-Liege-Bastogne-Liege-2024-350x233.jpeg 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/Grace-Brown-wins-Liege-Bastogne-Liege-2024.jpeg 2048w\" /><figcaption>A.S.O./Billy Ceusters</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>In the women’s Liège-Bastogne-Liège, Grace Brown (FDJ-Suez) broke away with Elise Chabbey (Canyon-SRAM) and Kim Cadzow (EF Education-Cannondale), eventually being absorbed by a strong chasing group as the race hit the final 10km. But Brown’s resilience was evident. Undeterred by a quick detour as she locked up coming out of a roundabout, she fought hard to reattach to the leading group with Cadzow in tow.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The win would be decided between this six-woman group, and what a selection of contenders it boasted. Kasia Niewiadoma (Canyon-SRAM), who recently ended an almost <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/kasia-niewiadoma-fleche-wallonne\" target=\"_blank\">five-year win drought at La Flèche Wallonne</a>, and teammate Chabbey, plus Tour of Flanders winner <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/elisa-longo-borghini-cyclist\" target=\"_blank\">Elisa Longo Borghini </a>(Lidl-Trek) and reigning champion Demi Vollering (SD Worx-Protime). An initial kick from Niewiadoma was neutralised by Longo Borghini. It looked like perhaps the two were clear to fight between themselves until a surging Brown came sprinting into the picture. She flew by Longo Borghini for victory. Twice second at Liège-Bastogne-Liège in 2020 and 2022, she finally made the top step with a roaring performance.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Closer to another women’s Milan-San Remo?</h2>\n\n\n\n<div><blockquote><p>Heard this too on RAI TV, women's Milan-Sanremo in the works, they added the Trofeo Binda will have to move to another slot <a href=\"https://t.co/cpYiqlo0zU\" target=\"_blank\">https://t.co/cpYiqlo0zU</a></p>— the Inner Ring (@inrng) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/inrng/status/1782073752735354970?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\" target=\"_blank\">April 21, 2024</a></blockquote> </div>\n\n\n\n<p>Rumors began to swirl on Twitter that RAI Sport has confirmed a women’s <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/tags/milan-san-remo\" target=\"_blank\">Milan-San Remo</a> for 2025, with Trofeo Alfredo Binda having to be moved to another slot on the calendar.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>RCS Sport had initially aimed to add a women’s Milan-San Remo in 2023, but that did not materialise. Hopefully this time it’s happening.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The last winner of a women’s Milan-San Remo – then called the Primavera Rosa – was Trixi Worrack for Equipe Nürnberger Versicherung in 2005.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Lorena Wiebes extends contract with SD Worx-Protime</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"646\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/Lorena-Wiebes-wins-in-Drenthe-970x646.jpeg\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/Lorena-Wiebes-wins-in-Drenthe-970x646.jpeg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/Lorena-Wiebes-wins-in-Drenthe-300x200.jpeg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/Lorena-Wiebes-wins-in-Drenthe-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/Lorena-Wiebes-wins-in-Drenthe-1536x1023.jpeg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/Lorena-Wiebes-wins-in-Drenthe-2048x1365.jpeg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/Lorena-Wiebes-wins-in-Drenthe-750x500.jpeg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/Lorena-Wiebes-wins-in-Drenthe-1140x760.jpeg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/Lorena-Wiebes-wins-in-Drenthe-465x310.jpeg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/Lorena-Wiebes-wins-in-Drenthe-620x413.jpeg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/03/Lorena-Wiebes-wins-in-Drenthe-350x233.jpeg 350w\" /><figcaption>SD Worx-Protime</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Lorena Wiebes has extended her contract with <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/tags/sd-worx\" target=\"_blank\">SD Worx-Protime</a> through 2028. The 25-year-old said, ‘I didn’t hesitate for long. I feel completely at home in this team and I also feel that in this environment I can make the necessary steps in the coming years.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>‘I get along well with Lotte [Kopecky]. In the races we strengthen each other… it’s a great prospect that we will still be together in a team for the next four years.’</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Wiebes has been with the squad since 2023 and in that short time she has racked up the wins including Ronde van Drenthe, Gent-Wevelgem, stage wins at the Giro d’Italia Donne and Tour de France Femmes, and she’s still the only winner of Scheldeprijs with four consecutive victories.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>See you next week.</p>\n\n\n<div>\r\n                <div>\r\n                   <div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <h4><span>Related Posts</span></h4>\r\n                      </div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <div>\r\n                            <div>\r\n                            <article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/kasia-niewiadoma-fleche-wallonne\">Kasia Niewiadoma is cycling’s latest example for why you should never give up</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/tadej-pogacar-monument-ranking\">Every Tadej Pogačar Monument performance ranked</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/giro-ditalia-watch-live-stages-route-riders-teams-start-list\">Giro d’Italia 2024: Stage-by-stage preview and how to watch</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article></div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <span></span><span></span><span></span>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                \r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        </div><p>The post <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/pro-cycling-news-liege-bastogne-liege-2024\">Pro Log: Tadej Pogačar and Grace Brown win Liège-Bastogne-Liège, women’s Milan-San Remo news and Lorena Wiebes extends SD Worx-Protime contract</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a>.</p>","author":"Robyn Davidson &#124; Editorial Assistant","siteTitle":"Cyclist.co.uk","siteHash":"561486e7070fa5351de9318ad0fa26c2a39332acba5fc7c7d1694a01d53d431e","entryHash":"5f93fcd647ddfaa605bf43b22f4389b6d079cdd4b1f6e8444445322bbd77c3d3","category":"Cycling"}